{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_26","type":"agent_message","text":"{\"reviewer\":\"codex\",\"schemaVersion\":1,\"scores\":null,\"weightedTotal\":null,\"verdict\":\"WARNING\",\"issues\":[{\"severity\":\"P3\",\"location\":\"prisma/schema.prisma:153\",\"description\":\"The new /api/spaces pagination query now filters ACTIVE spaces and orders by updatedAt desc, id desc, but Space still only has single-column indexes such as ownerId and status. At larger row counts, especially super-admin global listing, the database may still need an avoidable sort after filtering, so the response-size fix does not fully address query-plan scalability.\",\"recommendation\":\"Handle as a follow-up DB-performance WI: validate production query plans and add compound indexes that match the hot access paths, for example status + updatedAt desc + id desc for global listing and any owner/member scoped variants justified by EXPLAIN output.\",\"defer\":true,\"deferRationale\":\"This requires schema migration approval and environment-specific query-plan validation. WI-010's stated boundary is response size and cursor correctness, and the current patch fixes the immediate unbounded response risk without introducing a correctness or security blocker.\",\"fixNow\":false}]}"}}
